# Git Push Rules for TA-gen_ai_cim

## Repository Layout

The workspace lives at `/opt/splunk/etc/apps/TA-gen_ai_cim` but the git repo root is at `/opt/splunk/etc`. Two remotes are configured:

| Remote    | URL                                              | Purpose                           |
|-----------|--------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| `origin`  | https://github.com/mayeack/5GCoreAnalytics.git   | Parent repo (full Splunk etc/)    |
| `ta-cim`  | https://github.com/mayeack/TA-gen_ai_cim.git     | **Dedicated TA repo (primary)**   |

## Push Workflow

When the user asks to push, commit, or save to git, **ALWAYS** push to the `ta-cim` remote (https://github.com/mayeack/TA-gen_ai_cim). Follow these steps:

1. **Stage and commit** changes in `/opt/splunk/etc` for files under `apps/TA-gen_ai_cim/` only.
2. **Subtree push** to the dedicated repo:
   ```bash
   cd /opt/splunk/etc
   git subtree push --prefix=apps/TA-gen_ai_cim ta-cim main
   ```
3. If subtree push fails due to history divergence, use split + force push:
   ```bash
   cd /opt/splunk/etc
   git subtree split --prefix=apps/TA-gen_ai_cim -b ta-cim-split
   git push ta-cim ta-cim-split:main --force
   git branch -D ta-cim-split
   ```
4. **Do NOT push to `origin` (5GCoreAnalytics)** unless the user explicitly requests it.

## Remote Setup

If the `ta-cim` remote is missing, add it:
```bash
cd /opt/splunk/etc
git remote add ta-cim https://github.com/mayeack/TA-gen_ai_cim.git
```

## Excluded Files

Never commit these files:
- `.cursor/mcp.json` (instance-specific, may contain credentials)
- `local/` directory (Splunk local overrides)
- `lookups/*.csv` (user data, training data)

## Committed `.cursor/` Content

The following are intentionally tracked so the team shares the same IDE context:
- `.cursor/rules/` (project rules)
- `.cursor/skills/` (shared Cursor skills; symlinked from user-level `~/.cursor/skills/` for convenience)
